    base:desc "In a digital twin implementation following MBSE best practices, the development is partitioned into four primary abstraction levels. At the requirements level the twin’s functional and performance targets are captured in textual or SysML requirement diagrams. The functional architecture level is expressed through SysML Block Definition Diagrams and ACME components, mapping out the high‑level functional decomposition. The logical architecture is modeled with SysML IBDs, MontiArc connectors, and AADL to describe component interactions and data flows. The product/technical layer includes code generation, Simulink simulation models, and Java/C++ implementation. Transition between levels is traced via SysML model relationships to preserve consistency, while governance is achieved through iterative review cycles, stakeholder alignment, and traceability of changes."
