    base:desc "The digital twin relies on the Asset Administration Shell (AAS) as defined in the Plattform Industrie 4.0 “Details of the Asset Administration Shell” (2021). The AAS instance encapsulates ownership metadata, including the asset owner, legal domain, and governance policies. Access is controlled via a role‑based access control (RBAC) model embedded in the AAS profile, allowing fine‑grained read/write permissions and the definition of data sharing agreements. Optional privacy tags can be attached to data sets; these tags allow automated anonymisation and compliance with privacy regulations such as GDPR. Data in transit is protected by TLS 1.3 over MQTT (Mosquitto 2017) and data at rest is encrypted with AES‑256, combining encrypt‑then‑MAC security best practices."
